<br>
Tanik's trigger is not a trap-line, it's a spawned-monster with an aggro radius, no name, and a blank picture.  When you walk within the &quot;aggro&quot; radius, instead of an &quot;attack&quot; action like normal monsters, it triggers a &quot;spawn&quot; action that either spawns Tanik, or the Kromrif Death Squad (oh no, Mr Bill!)<br>
<br>
Because its a mob placeholder, when your pet is on guard, your pet will always spin to face the nearest player or NPC / monster.  In this case, it will spin to face the placeholder like you described.<br>
<br>
Another way to find Tanik is pick up a no-drop item from your inventory, and click around on the snow on your screen.  Because its a no-drop, you'll get a message that the item cannot be traded or dropped, standard stuff.  BUT, we also know if you are too far away to trade, and click an item, it prints &quot;you are too far away to trade&quot;.  You will see that as you click around, if you click on Tanik's placeholder, you WILL get a &quot;too far to trade&quot; message.  Which, also shows he's a mob, not a trap-line.<br>
<br>
But, it doesnt really matter, because Tanik only spawns in one of three places.  One at the very bottom of the ramp, where the wall does a sharp 90deg turn to the left, tanik spawns in the center of the ramp.  One at the top fo the ramp southwest of where the ramp starts sloping downward, like you mentioned in your post. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarionmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SarionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#333333>(7/9/01 7:36:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=735.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to find Tanik (4th shawl)</span><hr size=1> Very likely.  My first three spawns were to the north, all of them were Death Squad.  Then one to the SW, which was Tanik. <p>~~
